Server is up at http://localhost:5173/

Why this happens every time
npm run dev starts a local development server — it's a temporary process, not a system service. When your Mac sleeps:

macOS suspends/kills background terminal processes
Node.js (Vite) loses its network socket
When you wake up, the process is dead or zombie — port 5173 stops responding
This is normal for any local dev server (Vite, Next.js, etc.). It's not a crash or a bug.

Quick fix going forward
Each time you open your Mac to work, just run this in your terminal:

bash
npm run dev
If the port is stuck from a stale process, kill it first:

bash
pkill -f vite && npm run dev
Or you can just ask me to "start the server" and I'll handle it.